tickets.subject: SFP - 21166 - Customers are getting stuck in police sketch room due to hidden objects
tickets.raw_subject: SFP - 21166 - Customers are getting stuck in police sketch room due to hidden objects
tickets.description:
Customers are getting stuck in the corner of the sketch room and are not reachable by sims working at the police station. This seems to be due to the fact that a plant (hidden at lower sketch-room levels) is blocking working sims from reaching the customers (see 'before and after' screenshots attached).

Note: This is 100% reproducible when loading affected saves. CS can 'kill action' for the customer as a manual fix. 

STR (Example)
1. Load affected savefile
2. Go to the police station 
3. Notice customer in the corner of the sketch room 
4. Send a sim to work at the police station 
5. Select to serve the customer in the corner of the sketch room
6. Notice that the footprints symbol appears over the sim's head 
7. Use the debug menu to increase the level of the sketch room
8. Notice that a (future) plant is blocking access to the customer

tickets.subject: SFP - 19347 - Inconsistency is observed with the action duration shown and actual duration of action after upgrading buildable
tickets.raw_subject: SFP - 19347 - Inconsistency is observed with the action duration shown and actual duration of action after upgrading buildable
tickets.description:
Upon updating the buildable the action duration of the respective buildable decreases, it is observed that the action duration is different from the actual action duration when performing.

STR:
1. Start a new game.
2. Max out and skip tutorial.
3. Construct the Police station and trigger and complete Specialization training.
4. Upgrade any buildable to level 20.
5. Send a sim to job and assign sim with customer related to upgraded buildable.
Actual result: Action duration when performed is still the same even after upgrading the buildable.
Expected result: Action duration shown should be same to the action duration when assigned.

tickets.raw_subject: SFP - 18458 - Spa House built in the Mysterious Island is different from the Spa House built in the Sim Town
tickets.description:

STR:
1.	Install and launch the application.
2.	Complete the tutorials and reach level 11.
3.	Progress the game till the Parallel Quest The Mysterious Island gets completed

6.	Purchase the Spa House from the Personal Progress tab.
7.	Build the Spa House in the Mysterious Island house lots.

Expected Result: Same Spa House Template should be used in both Mysterious Island and Sim Town house lots.

tickets.subject: SFP - 19496 - All patio tiles will change even when 'no' is selected
tickets.raw_subject: SFP - 19496 - All patio tiles will change even when 'no' is selected
tickets.description:
When constructing a different-tiled patio next to an existing patio, selecting a tile to change all of the tiles to, then selecting 'no', all of the tiles will change to the same tile. This means that really expensive patios can be created by tacking-on a small expensive patio to a larger, cheaper patio and vice versa

See ticket #350598

tickets.subject: SFP - 19493 - Unable to move central rock decoration or benches in spa houses
tickets.raw_subject: SFP - 19493 - Unable to move central rock decoration or benches in spa houses
tickets.description:
The outdoor spa decorations (central rock and benches) cannot be moved in build mode. If the 'outdoors' section of build mode is open, when selecting the rock or benches and choosing to sell, a notification will pop up saying 'A patio can not be sold while a Sim is using an object placed on it. Have them stop, then try again' even though there is no sim present.
If a different tab of the homestore is open, then nothing will happen if the central rock or benches are tapped.

See ticket #350598

tickets.subject: SFP - 19488 - Town Value increases when visiting neighbouring towns
tickets.raw_subject: SFP - 19488 - Town Value increases when visiting neighbouring towns
tickets.description: Players are reporting that after visiting some neighbouring towns, their town value will increase. After testing a player's save (15651951) with their neighbour's save (19036389) by linking them to two in-house facebook accounts, it has been verified that the player's town value will increase by 282,000 after every visit to this town.

tickets.subject: SFP - 19214 - Sim relationship can progress to 'partner' before 'kiss on cheek' action is completed in 'Love is in the Air'
tickets.raw_subject: SFP - 19214 - Sim relationship can progress to 'partner' before 'kiss on cheek' action is completed in 'Love is in the Air'
tickets.description: It is possible for two sims to progress to 'partner' before the 'kiss on cheek' action is completed in the 'Love is in the Air' quest. When two sims become partners, the 'kiss on cheek' option disappears and they cannot complete the task. Players can either break up the two partnered sims and start over or they can progress relationships with different sims.

tickets.subject: SFP - 19152 - Red car appears in Latin Villa template preview for small house lots
tickets.raw_subject: SFP - 19152 - Red car appears in Latin Villa template preview for small house lots
tickets.description: If a player previews the Latin Villa house on a small lot, the red car will appear with it. However, the car does not come with the house when it is built. If a player previews the Latin Villa on a larger house lot, there will be no red car in the preview
